%20Police%20Department%20vehicle%20in%20Laguna%20Beach%2C%20California%2C%20U.S.%20in%20this%20handout%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a76b2c194a2d49b8aef423%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20NHTSA%20said%20in%20a%20notice%20that%20Tesla%20often%20takes%20months%20to%20report%20crash%20data%20that%20involves%20its%20driver%20assistance%20technologies.%3Cp%3ELaguna%20Beach%20Police%20Department%2FHandout%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENHTSA%20is%20investigating%20whether%20Tesla%20correctly%20reported%20crashes%20tied%20to%20Autopilot%20and%20FSD.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20regulator%20said%20Tesla%20said%20it%20was%20an%20issue%20with%20data%20collection%20that%20has%20now%20been%20remedied.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETesla%20and%20NHTSA%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20is%20once%20again%20in%20the%20crosshairs%20of%20federal%20regulators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Highway%20Traffic%20Safety%20Administration%20announced%20Wednesday%20that%20it%20is%20investigating%20allegations%20that%20Tesla%20is%20not%20correctly%20reporting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-deaths%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecrashes%20involving%20its%20Autopilot%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-fsd-diary-curiosity-amazement-shock-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFull%20Self-Driving%3C%2Fa%3E%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20probe%20notice%2C%20the%20NHTSA%20said%20that%20car%20companies%20are%20required%20to%20report%20crashes%20involving%20autonomous%20or%20advanced%20driver%20assistance%20systems%20within%20five%20days%20of%20being%20notified%20of%20them.%20The%20regulator%20alleged%20that%20Tesla%20submitted%20reports%20months%20after%20the%20incident%2C%20sometimes%20in%20batches%20or%20on%20a%20rolling%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPreliminary%20engagement%20between%20%5BOffice%20of%20Defects%20Investigation%5D%20and%20Tesla%20on%20the%20issue%20indicates%20that%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20reports%20was%20due%20to%20an%20issue%20with%20Tesla's%20data%20collection%2C%20which%2C%20according%20to%20Tesla%2C%20has%20now%20been%20fixed%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20NHTSA's%20notice.%20%26quot%3BNHTSA%20is%20opening%20this%20Audit%20Query%2C%20a%20standard%20process%20for%20reviewing%20compliance%20with%20legal%20requirements%2C%20to%20evaluate%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20potential%20delays%20in%20reporting%2C%20the%20scope%20of%20any%20such%20delays%2C%20and%20the%20mitigations%20that%20Tesla%20has%20developed%20to%20address%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NHTSA%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20O'Dowd%2C%20founder%20of%20The%20Dawn%20Project%2C%20a%20tech%20safety%20advocacy%20group%2C%20pointed%20out%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20according%20to%20Tesla's%20crash-counting%20methodology%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tesla.com%2FVehicleSafetyReport%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elisted%20on%20its%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20only%20counts%20crashes%20involving%20airbag%20deployments%20and%20if%20Autopilot%20was%20engaged%20within%20five%20seconds%20before%20the%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20NHTSA%20said%20it%20was%20investigating%20Tesla's%20Model%203%20and%20Model%20Y%20vehicles%20over%20an%20alleged%20phenomenon%20known%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-phantom-braking-autopilot-nhtsa-investigation-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ephantom%20braking%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20when%20the%20vehicle%20suddenly%20slams%20on%20the%20brakes%20for%20no%20reason%2C%20often%20at%20high%20speeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-ceo-elon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETesla%20CEO%20Elon%20Musk%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20on%20what%20was%20then%20Twitter%20that%20phantom%20braking%20would%20be%20fixed%20in%20a%20coming%20software%20update%2C%20but%20he%20has%20not%20commented%20further%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20August%201%2C%20a%20Florida%20judge%20ordered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-federal-trial-verdict-deadly-autopilot-crash-florida-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETesla%20to%20pay%20%24242%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20damages%20after%20finding%20the%20EV%20partly%20to%20blame%20for%20a%202019%20crash%20that%20killed%20a%2022-year-old%20woman%20and%20seriously%20injured%20her%20boyfriend.%20The%20driver%20was%20using%20Autopilot%20and%20had%20briefly%20looked%20away%20when%20the%20crash%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20said%20on%20X%20that%20the%20company%20would%20appeal%20the%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20lawsuit%20brought%20by%20California's%20Department%20of%20Motor%20Vehicles%20alleges%20that%20Tesla's%20use%20of%20language%20in%20advertising%20Autopilot%20and%20FSD%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-license-california-lawsuit-hearing-dmv-fsd-autopilot-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emisled%20consumers%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20thinking%20the%20vehicles%20are%20more%20autonomous%20than%20they%20really%20are.%20The%20case%20could%20see%20Tesla's%20right%20to%20sell%20in%20California%20suspended%20for%20at%20least%2030%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorney%20Matthew%20Benedetto%2C%20a%20member%20of%20Tesla's%20legal%20team%2C%20denied%20the%20allegations%20and%20told%20an%20administrative%20judge%20last%20month%20that%20the%20company%20informed%20customers%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bcannot%20fu