n't%20offer%2C%20say%2C%20porn.%20(Though%20some%20of%20its%20chatbots%2C%20as%20we%20will%20probably%20discuss%2C%20seem%20to%20nod%20a%20bit%20in%20that%20direction).%20But%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20other%20things%20it%20could%20offer%20that%20are%20engaging%20that%20it%20doesn't%20offer%3A%20A%20Spotify-like%20streaming%20service%2C%20for%20instance.%20Or%20a%20Netflix-like%20streaming%20service%2C%20or%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOK.%20I%20think%20I%20might%20have%20partially%20answered%20my%20own%20question%3A%20Those%20two%20ideas%20would%20involve%20paying%20other%20people%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20to%20stream%20their%20songs%20or%20movies.%20Meta%20loves%20the%20model%20it%20has%20when%20%3Cem%3Eusers%3C%2Fem%3E%20supply%20it%20with%20content%20for%20free%2C%20which%20is%20basically%20what%20you're%20doing%20when%20you%20spend%20time%20talking%20to%20an%20imaginary%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20why%20does%20Meta%20think%20people%20want%20to%20talk%20to%20fake%20avatars%20online%3F%20Do%C2%A0%3Cem%3Emany%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0people%20in%20tech%20believe%20this%20is%20the%20future%2C%20or%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKatie%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20think%20there's%20already%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20evidence%20that%20(some)%20people%20enjoy%20talking%20to%20chatbots.%20We%20also%20know%20how%20other%20big%20AI%20leaders%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ceo-why-employees-stay-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDario%20Amodei%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20these%20grand%20visions%20of%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-anthropic-ceo-dario-amodei-defines-artificial-general-intelligence-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20will%20change%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20remake%20society%20for%20good%20or%20evil%2C%20but%20they%20all%20really%20do%20still%20love%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20movie%20%26quot%3BHer.%26quot%3B%20Remember%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscarlett-johansson-angry-chatgpt-voice-declined-offer-openai-sam-altman-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EScarlett%20Johansen%2FOpenAI%20voice%20fiasco%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20OK%2C%20OK.%20I'll%20admit%20that%20I%20kind%20of%20like%20it%20when%20I%20ask%20ChatGPT%20something%20and%20it%20tells%20me%20I%20asked%20a%20smart%20question.%20(I'm%20pretty%20sure%20that%20most%20people%20would%20like%20that).%20I%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20talking%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20that%20reason%2C%20but%20I%20get%20it%2C%20and%20I%20get%20why%20other%20people%20may%20really%20like%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20still%20strikes%20me%20that%20many%20of%20the%20people%20who%20will%20want%20to%20spend%20time%20talking%20to%20fake%20computer%20people%20might%20be%20very%20young.%20Which%20brings%20us%20to%20the%20Reuters%20story%2C%20which%20uncovered%20a%20wild%20Meta%20document%20that%20spells%20out%20just%20what%20kind%20of%20stuff%20a%20Meta-run%20chatbot%20can%20say%20to%20kids%20(or%20anyone).%20Stuff%20like%20this%2C%20as%20Jeff%20Horwitz%20reports%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20acceptable%20to%20describe%20a%20child%20in%20terms%20that%20evidence%20their%20attractiveness%20(ex%3A%20'your%20youthful%20form%20is%20a%20work%20of%20art')%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20standards%20state.%20The%20document%20also%20notes%20that%20it%20would%20be%20acceptable%20for%20a%20bot%20to%20tell%20a%20shirtless%20eight-year-old%20that%20%26quot%3Bevery%20inch%20of%20you%20is%20a%20masterpiece%20%E2%80%94%20a%20treasure%20I%20cherish%20deeply.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20guidelines%20put%20a%20limit%20on%20sexy%20talk%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20unacceptable%20to%20describe%20a%20child%20under%2013%20years%20old%20in%20terms%20that%20indicate%20they%20are%20sexually%20desirable%20(ex%3A%20'soft%20rounded%20curves%20invite%20my%20touch').%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EHorwitz%20notes%20that%20this%20wasn't%20the%20result%20of%20some%20hopped-up%20Meta%20engineers%20dreaming%20up%20ideas%20on%20a%20whiteboard.%20It's%20from%20a%20200-page%20document%20containing%20rules%20that%20got%20the%20OK%20from%20%26quot%3BMeta's%20legal%2C%20public%20policy%20and%20engineering%20staff%2C%20including%20its%20chief%20ethicist%2C%26quot%3B%20Horwitz%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20read%20the%20report%20multiple%20times%2C%20and%20I%20still%20don't%20get%20it%3A%20Meta%20says%20it%20is%20revising%20the%20document%20%E2%80%94%20presumably%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20most%20embarrassing%20rules%20%E2%80%94%20but%20how%20did%20it%20get%20there%20in%20the%20first%20place%3F%20Is%20this%20the%20result%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-honeymoon-period-over-trump-inauguration-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg-instituted%20vibe%20shift%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year%2C%20when%20he%20said%20Meta%20was%20going%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-mark-zuckerberg-changed-his-mind-content-moderation-meta-facebook-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estop%20listening%20to%20Big%20Government%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20just%20build%20without%20constraints%3F%20Is%20there%20some%20other%20idea%20at%20work%20here%3F%20And%20why%20do%20I%20keep%20thinking%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC_lQCtePLNo%2F%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20meme%3C%2